00:08:44.855 --> 00:08:46.644
CHARLES: Exactly.

00:08:46.644 --> 00:08:50.180
Well you know this is actually
a case of an example of the

00:08:50.180 --> 00:08:52.020
convergent evolution
that we had.

00:08:52.020 --> 00:08:55.060
And this is why when Josh and
I finally decided to work

00:08:55.060 --> 00:08:57.863
together, we went through
this a few times, trying

00:08:57.863 --> 00:09:00.660
to merge our work.

00:09:00.660 --> 00:09:05.260
But once you get under the skin,
we realized that how we

00:09:05.260 --> 00:09:06.880
were doing it was
quite different.

00:09:06.880 --> 00:09:10.040
Every time it just seemed
like too much trouble.

00:09:10.040 --> 00:09:13.910
So Josh is doing this, I
believe, in JavaScript all in

00:09:13.910 --> 00:09:15.090
the client side.

00:09:15.090 --> 00:09:19.520
What I was doing was I was
posting about JSON to an

00:09:19.520 --> 00:09:24.850
Apache server, and running PHP
to parche the text and to come

00:09:24.850 --> 00:09:27.610
up with the random die results,
and then posting that

00:09:27.610 --> 00:09:31.310
back and to the client, and
from there into the shared

00:09:31.310 --> 00:09:35.290
state, and then pushing
it to everybody else.

00:09:35.290 --> 00:09:38.350
So two totally different ways
of doing exactly the same

00:09:38.350 --> 00:09:41.000
thing, but when it came down to
an integrating one with the

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:42.816
other, it was just apples
and oranges.

00:09:46.216 --> 00:09:48.640
ALLEN: And that's part of why
I asked the question is

00:09:48.640 --> 00:09:51.280
because there are obviously a
lot of different approaches

00:09:51.280 --> 00:09:52.550
that can go with it.

00:09:52.550 --> 00:09:55.350
I want to know which one you
guys chose, and kind of your

00:09:55.350 --> 00:09:57.870
thinking behind why
you chose that.

00:09:57.870 --> 00:10:03.020
And especially when you're
talking games, how do you find

00:10:03.020 --> 00:10:05.190
the right a comfort level
between security and

00:10:05.190 --> 00:10:05.850
playability.

00:10:05.850 --> 00:10:09.800
JOSHUA: Right, OK so for the
main mechanism of how we're

00:10:09.800 --> 00:10:13.430
actually sharing everything,
first of all, we are using the

00:10:13.430 --> 00:10:15.320
shared state objects.

00:10:15.320 --> 00:10:20.100
It does have a limit of the 10K
size, so we actually don't

00:10:20.100 --> 00:10:22.760
share when you add
an image there.

00:10:22.760 --> 00:10:26.860
We just share the event that
player X added an image, and

00:10:26.860 --> 00:10:29.520
then in the shared state object
we share out the URL,

00:10:29.520 --> 00:10:32.130
the size of image, the location
of the image, and we

00:10:32.130 --> 00:10:34.700
essentially replay that
on all of the clients.

00:10:34.700 --> 00:10:37.040
So we're using the state
object kind of

00:10:37.040 --> 00:10:37.760
like an event engine.

00:10:37.760 --> 00:10:40.790
And as soon as it processes that
event from that person,

00:10:40.790 --> 00:10:43.952
it clears it from the state.

00:10:43.952 --> 00:10:48.660
CHARLES: So the two aspects of
this is that are that you've

00:10:48.660 --> 00:10:51.610
got a limit of 10K in the shared
state, which needs to

00:10:51.610 --> 00:10:53.970
be very conservative about what
you put in there, and you

00:10:53.970 --> 00:10:57.710
have to clean it up when
you're done with it.

00:10:57.710 --> 00:11:00.240
And then the other thing is,
that because there's so many

00:11:00.240 --> 00:11:05.010
browsers, cross browser
compatibility becomes a big

00:11:05.010 --> 00:11:10.780
issue, which is why I chose
to go the JSON PHP route.

00:11:10.780 --> 00:11:14.060
Because once you're at PHP,
you're on a server that's

00:11:14.060 --> 00:11:14.770
completely separate.

00:11:14.770 --> 00:11:17.230
You know what the environment
is, and it always works the

00:11:17.230 --> 00:11:18.410
same every single time.

00:11:18.410 --> 00:11:22.760
As long as you can do the JSON
event, and parse the result on

00:11:22.760 --> 00:11:25.510
every browser, it doesn't
matter what it

00:11:25.510 --> 00:11:26.960
is that you're doing.

00:11:26.960 --> 00:11:31.475
So we're still in the process
of working this out.

00:11:31.475 --> 00:11:34.940
The Tabletop Forge has turned
